 have done such and such s=\r\nadhana, and also zero mantra-chaitanya comes to a person.. Mantra chaitanya=\r\n is a very rare things. The mantra will actually reveal itself in all the p=\r\nlanes. It is the real effect of genuine purusacharana. Of course, mantra-ch=\r\naitanya can come through other methods too. Purusacharana is one method amo=\r\nng many.\n\nIn olden times when a person would *successfully* complete a cert=\r\nain Purusacharana, they would be conferred a higher level of abhisekh. Nowa=\r\ndays, frankly and mostly, all that happens in the name of Purusacharana in =\r\nparamparas is by hook or crook just finish a prescribed number of japa/homa=\r\n and then be given a title and then feel happy and proud about it internall=\r\ny. I have met some people like that. All have heavy titles attached to thei=\r\nr names, this and that. It does not make the person genuinely spiritual at =\r\nall, for the heart of the purusacharana practice has already been lost.\n\n\nF=\r\nor ordinary people like us, doing japa, as you mentioned below, more and mo=\r\nre is very good. It purifies us. One can do it at all times, do it under th=\r\ne breath. Eventually it can become a background process in your life. Moreo=\r\nver, when you do mindful japa, that is even superb. It is a meditation in i=\r\ntself. It can be done even while moving and beauty of the mantra will keep =\r\ntickling in. Not thinking of sadhana in technical terms and rather as a ser=\r\nvice to ones Istha makes the japa even more powerful and beautiful.\n\n\nInfac=\r\nt, if we mindfully do every action - no doubt difficult initially - then li=\r\nke Swami Sivananda says, everything becomes an act of sadhana!\n\n-Regards\n=\r\n=C2=A0Rajarshi\n\n\nawaktam wyaktimApannam manyantE mAmabuddhayah |\nparam bhAw=\r\namajAnanto mamAwyayamanuttamam ||[7:24]\n\n\n________________________________\n=\r\n From: sunrise_1080 &lt;sunrise_1080@...&gt;\nTo: vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups=\r\n.com \nSent: Tuesday, 23 October 