g. These also correspond to the consciousness workin=\r\ng in manomaya-kosha, pranamaya-kosha and annamaya-kosha. Until this is reac=\r\nhed, grace does not come, and even if it does, it gets perverted by our low=\r\ner nature. In Gita Bhagawan calls it Apara-Prakriti. \n&gt; \n&gt; It is one thing =\r\nto say verbally that all sadhana being done is work of God&#39;s Shakti. It is =\r\nentirely different matter to see it clearly for which one must a) surrender=\r\n constantly b) reject and withdraw ones lower nature, or at least keep it c=\r\nlam and checked c) make a sincere call to God. Only when these three work t=\r\nogether, grace descends. And only grace has the power to cause a thorough t=\r\nransformation of a sadhaka. Nothing less. But you can&#39;t demand grace, you c=\r\nan&#39;t beg for grace, you can&#39;t plead, you can&#39;t command, and you can&#39;t indul=\r\nge in self-pity. We have to calmly and patiently wait for it for when the t=\r\nime is right, it calls like a sweet rain on a parched throat, and in a flas=\r\nh it can do more than what we can imagine. Basically, we cannot negotiate w=\r\nith God. Nothing less than a complete honest recoking on what we are, where=\r\n we are heading, what mistakes lie in our nature is a must.\n&gt; \n&gt; Then slowl=\r\ny you will be made to realize the working of a higher Power that has nothin=\r\ng to do with your little surface personalities push and pulls based on Pavl=\r\novian responses to situations incurred over lifetimes. It is this Power, on=\r\nce understood, that needs to be unquestioningly submitted to in a progressi=\r\nve manner, while rejecting everything else inside us that pull us in a diff=\r\nerent direction and wants to hang on to our earlier flawed personality. Lon=\r\ng, long, long road. Patience is a key.\n&gt; \n&gt; *=C3=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0 *=C3=\r\n=82=C2=A0=C3=82=C2=A0 *\n&gt; \n&gt; A few general thoughts on Purusacharana since =\r\nthere were a few mails on this topic. Again, just my opinion. Feel free to =\r\nreject it if needed.\n&gt; \n&gt; Start with the word. Purusha+acharana. Behaving l=\r\nike a man. And what does it mean? Some may say it means being brave, being =\r\nmentally robust, being aggressive, or being commanding etc. All these are t=\r\nerms that are often used in colloquial language to indicate a proverbial &#39;m=\r\nanly&#39; behavior. But in sadhana, Purusha is a different concept. Looking inw=\r\nards and separating a part of your being, from the mind, from your thoughts=\r\n, from your emotions, and even from your physcial nature. This part of your=\r\n being will only stand back and watch, as silent witness, and then either g=\r\nive or reject consent to various movements of your lower nature (lust, ange=\r\nr, jealousy, greed, covetousness, ETC). Once this is firmly installed in yo=\r\nur system - this Purusha - it will be able to stop and clam down various pa=\r\nrts of your being which have the tendency to leap-up in joy (sukha) or get =\r\ndeflated (dukhkha) at surface appearances and shallow understandings. This =\r\nis how a Purusha\n&gt;  works in Yoga. When this kind of Purusha consciounsess =\r\nis installed and established, an expansion of the mind happens beyond the r=\r\national, the emotional or even the physical nature/consciousness.\n&gt; \n&gt; Afte=\r\nr this basic step has been done properly, then the sadhana of purushacharan=\r\na is to be done. By this method, a progressive 1/10 numerical deduction in =\r\nthe sadhana is done for each element. That is for 1000 japas, 100 homas, 10=\r\n tarpana, 1 marjana and finally feeding people. Each of this will affect a =\r\nrealization of the mantra is each of the layers - in reverse order from ann=\r\namaya-kosha, to pranamaya-kosha, to manomaya-kosha to vigyanmaya-kosha (the=\r\n spiritual layers beyond and above the reasoning mind). THAT is the perfect=\r\n effect of a spotless purushacharana. That is mantra siddhi and mantra chai=\r\ntanya.\n&gt; \n&gt; While doing a purushacharana, tremenodus amount of obstacles wi=\r\nll come in the path of the sadhaka. To overcome these, while sticking to th=\r\ne exacting rules of the sadhana, one MUST have done the first step properly=\r\n, that is installed a Purusha consciousness in his/her system, one that is =\r\nunshakeable in any adverse conditions. One that is perfectly unmoved by the=\r\n working of the lower nature in man as well as outside man. For example, on=\r\ne may get affected by high fever, various crisis situations, various attack=\r\ns from hostile forces etc etc, Many things. But inspite of that the Purusha=\r\n consciouness, if it has been firmly established, will drive the sadhana wi=\r\nthout a glitch, remaining unmoved. Of course, one must honestly judge how f=\r\nar such a consciousness has been developed. Self-delusion has to be guarded=\r\n against.\n&gt; \n&gt; One can try for oneself to do purushacharanas and see how fa=\r\nr one succeeds. In my opinion though, 98 % of seekers in this age are unfit=\r\n to do purushacharana and succeed in this sadhana. For the Purusha consciou=\r\nsness has not been established in the system by most people. In the last 6 =\r\nyears among all varieties of sadhakas I have met, of various paths, only tw=\r\no were there who I felt can pull off a genuine purusacharana. Rest no chanc=\r\ne.\n&gt; \n&gt; Doing any sadhana at the same time, same place, using same material=\r\ns, without breaks for years and years is always good. Goes without saying. =\r\nThis too, most people cannot do flawlessly. Purushacharana is far more comp=\r\nlex and demanding. \n&gt; \n&gt; Then the other option is to develop genuine surren=\r\nder from the deepest part of your heart. Do sadhana, and wait patiently. He=\r\nr grace is bound to come and illuminate the path. Meanhile, we can keep wor=\r\nking on rectifying the lower nature in ourselves.\n&gt; \n&gt; Jai Ma Tara.\n&gt; \n&gt; -R=\r\negards\n&gt; =C3=82=C2=A0Rajarshi\n&gt; \n&gt; \n&gt