t. This leads to confusions.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Anyway grace is =\r\nproduct of true surrenderance from the mind, from the deeper emotional bein=\r\ng and the physical being. These also correspond to the consciousness workin=\r\ng in manomaya-kosha, pranamaya-kosha and annamaya-kosha. Until this is reac=\r\nhed, grace does not come, and even if it does, it gets perverted by our low=\r\ner nature. In Gita Bhagawan calls it Apara-Prakriti. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; It=\r\n is one thing to say verbally that all sadhana being done is work of God&#39;s =\r\nShakti. It is entirely different matter to see it clearly for which one mus=\r\nt a) surrender constantly b) reject and withdraw ones lower nature, or at l=\r\neast keep it clam and checked c) make a sincere call to God. Only when thes=\r\ne three work together, grace descends. And only grace has the power to caus=\r\ne a thorough transformation of a sadhaka. Nothing less. But you can&#39;t deman=\r\nd grace, you can&#39;t beg for grace, you can&#39;t plead, you can&#39;t command, and y=\r\nou can&#39;t indulge in self-pity. We have to calmly and patiently wait for it =\r\nfor when the time is right, it calls like a sweet rain on a parched throat,=\r\n and in a flash it can do more than what we can imagine. Basically, we cann=\r\not negotiate with God. Nothing less than a complete honest recoking on what=\r\n we are, where we are heading, what mistakes lie in our nature is a must.&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Then slowly you will be made to realize the working of a =\r\nhigher Power that has nothing to do with your little surface personalities =\r\npush and pulls based on Pavlovian responses to situations incurred over lif=\r\netimes. It is this Power, once understood, that needs to be unquestioningly=\r\n submitted to in a progressive manner, while rejecting everything else insi=\r\nde us that pull us in a different direction and wants to hang on to our ear=\r\nlier flawed personality. Long, long, long road. Patience is a key.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;=\r\n &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; *=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp; *=C3=82&nbsp;=C3=82&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;=\r\nbr&gt;\n&gt; A few general thoughts on Purusacharana since there were a few mai=\r\nls on this topic. Again, just my opinion. Feel free to reject it if needed.=\r\n&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Start with the word. Purusha+acharana. Behaving like a =\r\nman. And what does it mean? Some may say it means being brave, being mental=\r\nly robust, being aggressive, or being commanding etc. All these are terms t=\r\nhat are often used in colloquial language to indicate a proverbial &#39;manly&#39; =\r\nbehavior. But in sadhana, Purusha is a different concept. Looking inwards a=\r\nnd separating a part of your being, from the mind, from your thoughts, from=\r\n your emotions, and even from your physcial nature. This part of your being=\r\n will only stand back and watch, as silent witness, and then either give or=\r\n reject consent to various movements of your lower nature (lust, anger, jea=\r\nlousy, greed, covetousness, ETC). Once this is firmly installed in your sys=\r\ntem - this Purusha - it will be able to stop and clam down various parts of=\r\n your being which have the tendency to leap-up in joy (sukha) or get deflat=\r\ned (dukhkha) at surface appearances and shallow understandings. This is how=\r\n a\n Purusha&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;  works in Yoga. When this kind of Purusha consciounses=\r\ns is installed and established, an expansion of the mind happens beyond the=\r\n rational, the emotional or even the physical nature/consciousness.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt=\r\n; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; After this basic step has been done properly, then the sadhana =\r\nof purushacharana is to be done. By this method, a progressive 1/10 numeric=\r\nal deduction in the sadhana is done for each element. That is for 1000 japa=\r\ns, 100 homas, 10 tarpana, 1 marjana and finally feeding people. Each of thi=\r\ns will affect a realization of the mantra is each of the layers - in revers=\r\ne order from annamaya-kosha, to pranamaya-kosha, to manomaya-kosha to vigya=\r\nnmaya-kosha (the spiritual layers beyond and above the reasoning mind). THA=\r\nT is the perfect effect of a spotless purushacharana. That is mantra siddhi=\r\n and mantra chaitanya.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; While doing a purushacharana, tre=\r\nmenodus amount of obstacles will come in the path of the sadhaka. To overco=\r\nme these, while sticking to the exacting rules of the sadhana, one MUST hav=\r\ne done the first step properly, that is installed a Purusha consciousness i=\r\nn his/her system, one that is unshakeable in any adverse conditions. One th=\r\nat is perfectly unmoved by the working of the lower nature in man as well a=\r\ns outside man. For example, one may get affected by high fever, various cri=\r\nsis situations, various attacks from hostile forces etc etc, Many things. B=\r\nut inspite of that the Purusha consciouness, if it has been firmly establis=\r\nhed, will drive the sadhana without a glitch, remaining unmoved. Of course,=\r\n one must honestly judge how far such a consciousness has been developed. S=\r\nelf-delusion has to be guarded against.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; One can try for =\r\noneself to do purushacharanas and see how far one succeeds. In my opinion t=\r\nhough, 98 % of seekers in this age are unfit to do purushacharana and succe=\r\ned in this sadhana. For the Purusha consciousness has not been established =\r\nin the system by most people. In the last 6 years among all varieties of sa=\r\ndhakas I have met, of various paths, only two were there who I felt can pul=\r\nl off a genuine purusacharana. Rest no chance.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Doing any=\r\n sadhana at the same time, same place, using same materials, without breaks=\r\n for years and years is always good. Goes without saying. This too, most pe=\r\nople cannot do flawlessly. Purushacharana is far more complex and demanding=\r\n. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Then the other option is to develop genuine surrender=\r\n from the deepest part of your heart. Do sadhana, and wait patiently. Her g=\r\nrace is bound to come and illuminate the path. Meanhile, we can keep workin=\r\ng on rectifying the lower nature in ourselves.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Jai Ma Ta=\r\nra.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; -Regards&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =C3=82&nbsp;Rajarshi&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;=\r\n\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =C3=82&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; awaktam=\r\n wyaktimApannam manyantE mAmabuddhayah |&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; param bhAwamajAnanto mamA=\r\nwyayamanuttamam ||[7:24]&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; _____________________=\r\n___________&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;  From: sunrise_1080 &lt;sunrise_1080@...&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =\r\nTo: &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; ymailto=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot; t=\r\narget=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot;&gt;vedic-wisdo=\r\nm@yahoogroups.com&lt;/a&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Sent: Tuesday, 23 October 2012 3:07 PM&lt;br&gt;\n=\r\n&gt; Subject: [vedic-wisdom] Re:&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;  &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =C3=82&nbsp;=\r\n &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Namaste Rajarshiji,&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; That is a very interestin=\r\ng way of looking at a yantra. I didn&#39;t know that before....thanks! I think =\r\nmost of us would agree with your mail, that spiritual success depends on pe=\r\nrsonal effort and God&#39;s grace.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; As an aside, it really do=\r\nes feel that our &#39;personal&#39; effort is also the Grace of God..! This is an a=\r\nge old statement....but of course, not meant as an excuse not to work hard =\r\non ourselves.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; I agree we have to keep striving....&#39;perso=\r\nnal&#39; effort has to continue...what a mahabharatha this inner fight is! Defi=\r\nnitely need