aybe relevant to his line of spiritual inquiry followed in =\r\nhis tradition) who do homas without doing any pre-requisite japa. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt;=\r\n &gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; One honest question that every sadhaka must ask himsel=\r\nf/herself objectively is, how badly do we want God? If the desire pure and =\r\nunblemished, or is it also mixed with various other desires, however small =\r\nthey maybe. If we also want other materialistic things along with it - and =\r\nthere is no harm in wanting legitimate things - then one can follow all ins=\r\ntructions and rules set for whatever parampara one is mentally afflicted to=\r\n and given by his/her Guru(s). &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; But if one is =\r\ndesirous of ONLY God without any other desire attached to it, no rule is su=\r\nfficient, no path is a guarantee, no sadhana is sure-shot way to achieve it=\r\n.=C3=83=E2=80=9A=C3=82&nbsp; Working on internal surrender to God and incre=\r\nased detachment in daily life along with and through whatever ritual one pe=\r\nrforms and in whatever manner, can be more helpful in the long run. Human a=\r\nspiration alone is not enough. When the aspiration is genuine and pure, He/=\r\nShe extends his/her energy to lift the sadhak up.. this dual phenomenon tog=\r\nether make a sadhana success. And this simple yet powerful truth is represe=\r\nnted by the six-pointed triangle which is the basic yantra of so many deiti=\r\nes, and specially one form of the Mother. The upward triangle is our aspira=\r\ntion, the downward is Her grace coming down to transform the sadhak from hi=\r\ns/her current state. Together, it makes a complete whole. And grace is pure=\r\nly proportional to the purity of the aspiration, which\n only God can judge&lt;=\r\nbr&gt;\n&gt; &gt;  accurately.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; -Regards&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &=\r\ngt; =C3=83=E2=80=9A=C3=82&nbsp;Rajarshi &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt; &lt;br&gt;\n=\r\n&gt; &gt; awaktam 